    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-07-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">[Telegram]</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Count
                        Wydenhruck.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-07-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 3, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I regret to say United States consul, Matamoras, wrote despatch June 27, received
                    to-day, namely :</p>
                <p>Maximilian was executed on the 19th; city of Mexico surrendered on 21st.</p>
                <p>United States consul, Vera Cruz, wrote despatch received and telegraphed from New
                    Orleans July 2, confirming the execution of Maximilian and surrender at
                    discretion of the city of Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Count <hi rend="smallcaps">Wydenbruck</hi>, &amp;c., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
